Our vinyl decals are used to enhance your home decor with inspirational, motivational, and comforting messages.  Their messages can also bring joy to you and your family as you use them to decorate for each holiday season (Valentine's Day, 4th of July, Halloween, Thanksgiving, Christmas), or wedding celebration.  Each and every vinyl decal is made with high attention to detail in order to provide you with the very best product.  It is important to me that you are proud of your purchase and happy to display it in your home.  I started this business in 2012 because of my love for vinyl and the beauty it brings to all home decor and I hope it brings you joy in your home.

Our removable vinyl decals are a matte finish and can be a great addition to your home decor with application to a wall, window, mirror, front door, interior door, finished or painted wood.  My two favorite places to apply the vinyl are to a wall or door. A family favorite are the toilet vinyl decals for holidays.

To see our Christmas hanging ornament decal click the link below...
https://www.etsy.com/listing/209388442/hanging-ornaments-toilet-vinyl-christmas?ref=shop_home_active_7&frs=1 

Wondering how vinyl decals are applied?  Here are the application instructions that will be included with your purchase...

APPLICATION INSTRUCTIONS

1.  Clean the surface you wish to apply the vinyl to, to remove any dust or dirt.  This will allow the vinyl to stick better to the surface.
2.  Measure and mark as a guide to ensure your vinyl goes on straight.
3.  Anchor the top of the vinyl with tape in multiple positions.
4.  Rub saying with the card provided.  Flip layer up and remove the bottom layer.  Start at the top and smooth down.  (If your phrase is long, you might want to cut it into smaller pieces after you have attached it with tape.)
5.  Rub vinyl again with card and begin to remove adhesive cover.  Remove slowly and carefully so the vinyl does not get torn or stretched.
6.  Congratulations!  You just applied your vinyl.

PLEASE NOTE:  Applying vinyl to surfaces with a matte finish requires extra care and attention to ensure the vinyl adheres to the surface during transfer tape removal.
